<pb xml:id="p001" facs="oscys.case.0119.001.001.jpg"/>

<div2 type="caption">

<p>To the Honorable Circuit Court of the District of Columbia, sitting in and for Washington County</p>

</div2>

<div2 type="body">

<p>The Petition of Elisa Johnson of said County of Washington respectfully states that she is a free woman of color and that Thomas B. Belt of said County has taken her into his possession, has confined her in jail of said County. <del>and</del> claims her as his slave and that he has done it <unclear reason="illegible">with</unclear> <gap extent="one word" reason="illegible"/> of disposing of yr Petitioner <del>out</del> as his slave, contrary to her rights and she therefor prays yr honors to cite said Thos <del>B.</del> I. Belt as the Law directs and that yr Petitioner's case may be inquired into and that she may be returned to her liberty as a free woman and as in duty bound will every pray &amp;c</p>

<p>Brent &amp; Brent atty for Petitioner</p>

<p>5 Aug 1840</p>

</div2>

<pb xml:id="p002" facs="oscys.case.0119.001.002.jpg"/>

<div2 type="back">

<p>305</p>

<p>Elisa Johnson<lb/>
vs<lb/>
Thomas B. Belt</p>

<p>Petition for freedom</p>

<p>Filed 6th August 1840</p>

</div2>

</div1>
    
